<subSubSection id="C335652B69588F5FFF4BFCA2FB478797" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B9036A069588F5FFF4BFCA2FB478797" blockId="18.[151,1437,151,897]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis id="B95BEAB269588F5FFF4BFCA2FEEE874A" bold="true" box="[199,332,834,860]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Discussion.</emphasis>
The strong ocellar setae of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F4D2369588F5FFDF3FCA3FC97874B" authority="Burington, 2022" authorityName="Burington" authorityYear="2022" box="[639,821,835,861]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Eucelatoria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="huitepecensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B95BEAB269588F5FFDF3FCA3FC97874B" box="[639,821,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">E. huitepecensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B95BEAB269588F5FFCB7FCA3FC36874B" bold="true" box="[827,916,835,861]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A26857C969588F5FFCB7FCA3FC36874B" box="[827,916,835,861]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
suggest an affinity closer to 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F4D2369588F5FFB58FCA3FA89874B" authorityName=": Wood" authorityYear="1985" box="[1236,1323,835,861]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Eucelatoria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferox">
<emphasis id="B95BEAB269588F5FFB58FCA3FA89874B" box="[1236,1323,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">E. ferox</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
than to 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F4D2369588F5FFA08FCA3FF478797" authority="Burington, 2022" authorityName="Burington" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Eucelatoria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inclani" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B95BEAB269588F5FFA08FCA3FF478797" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">E. inclani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B95BEAB269588F5FFF60FC87FEE78797" bold="true" box="[236,325,871,897]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A26857C969588F5FFF60FC87FEE78797" box="[236,325,871,897]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, but the partially fused, narrowly separated longitudinal thoracic vittae are unique.
</paragraph>
